    {
      "id": "sybil_9_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_9",
      "description": "Presenting an investment-grade 997.2 Carrera S, a definitive example of the final hydraulic-steering 911 era. This specimen is powered by the 3.8L MA1.01 flat-six featuring Direct Fuel Injection (DFI), delivering a linear power band and exceptional thermal efficiency. The drivetrain is anchored by a precise 6-speed manual transaxle and a factory-fitted mechanical limited-slip differential. Performance is enhanced by Porsche Active Suspension Management (PASM), providing a 10mm lower ride height and active damping. A recent DME report shows zero ignitions in ranges 2 through 6, confirming meticulous rev-limit adherence. The chassis remains factory-spec with no modifications, showcasing pristine bushings and a dry undercarriage. This is a turn-key, concours-quality vehicle for the purist who demands mechanical perfection and analog feedback.",
